posts.author: KuzoKevin
posts.title: Retard Finder for the win -

posts.raw_content:
absolutely nowhere.

ICE showed up in 5 trucks. First they pushed into my office and I met them there while they started reviewing employment records. It quickly became apparent that they'd received an anonymous tip that I was employing illegals. But when they saw my orderly employment files and all the E-verify posters, they slowed their roll. We went out to the coffee fields to interview a few of my guys, who were able to show their driver's licenses proving they were born in the US (some here, some stateside), or had valid green cards. We made sure everybody was ready just in case this happened, and my guys did us proud.

It was all over in less than an hour.  The agents were polite, completely pleasant, and even complimented me on running a tight ship. "I wish every farm was keeping records like this one," they told me. I'm sure the huge TRUMP 2028 flag on the warehouse wall didn't hurt either. I'll admit I was shaken when they left, though. They were big, aggressive guys, about half of them special agents in from the States, and they were not messing around - I could only imagine how it would feel if I had been on the wrong side of the law.

I am pretty sure I know who called in the tip, by the way. He's been after my upper field for years now. Pucho, you are going DOWN. I know about those illegal Dominicans you've been using at your warehouse. This time, I am not calling it in as an anonymous tip. I've got the business card of the field agent who's going to be banging on *your* door.

I'm sharing this story here because you lads understand. I hope you know that, just as in California and other liberal wastelands, you've got brothers everywhere, including the coffee fields of Puerto Rico.
